    "summary": "Prof. Dr. Hans van Kranenburg is working as a full professor in Corporate Strategy at Nijmegen School of Management of Radboud University Nijmegen. Van Kranenburg was working as an associate professor of Strategy and Industrial Organization at Maastricht University, the Netherlands. He has been a visiting professor at Oxford University (Reuters Institute & department of Politics and International Relations & Green Tempelton College (UK), University of Navarra (Spain) and at Media Management and Transformation Center at J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping University (Sweden) and visiting scholar at National Opinion Research Center affiliated with the University of Chicago (USA). He received his BA (Agricultural Economics) from the University of Exeter and his MA (Econometrics) from Tilburg University (the Netherlands). His Ph.D in Industrial Economics is from Maastricht University. He published on strategic behaviour of companies, nonmarket strategies, industry dynamics, alliances and networks, foreign direct investments. He is also an expert in media management and economics. Furthermore, he also advised companies such as publishing and chemical companies. He has previously published in international journals like Journal of Law and Economics, Journal of International Business Studies, International Business Review, Global Strategy Journal, British Journal of Management, International Studies of Management and Organization, Journal of Media Economics, Journal of Media Business Studies, Telecommunications Policy, Food Policy, Technological Forcasting and Social Change, Scandinavian Management Journal, Managerial and Decision Economics, Review of Industrial Organization, International Journal of Industrial Organization,  European Journal of Operational Research, Research Policy .\n\nHe also published books: Nonmarket Strategic Management (2017); Innovation Policies in the European News Media Industry (2017);  Management and Innovation in the Media Industry (2008).",
